  <mainDescription>&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;>&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Candara;&quot;>Requirements are often grouped to allow for further refinement as they
        are elaborated. These may include:&lt;/span>&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Candara;&quot;>&lt;br />
        &lt;/span>&lt;/font> 
        &lt;ul>
            &lt;li>
                &lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;>&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Candara;&quot;>Business requirements - the higher-level needs of the
                organization, such as the business issues or opportunities, and reasons why a project has been &lt;font
                size=&quot;4&quot;>undertaken.&lt;/font>&lt;/span>&lt;/font>
            &lt;/li>
            &lt;li>
                &lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;>&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Candara;&quot;>Stakeholder requirements - the needs of a
                stakeholder(s)&lt;/span>&lt;/font>
            &lt;/li>
            &lt;li>
                &lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;>&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Candara;&quot;>Solution requirements - the features, functions, and overall
                characteristics of the solution or product. These are often broken down into functional and nonfunctional
                requirements:&lt;/span>&lt;/font>
            &lt;/li>
            &lt;li>
                &lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;>&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Candara;&quot;>Functional requirements - the behaviors of the
                product.&lt;/span>&lt;/font>
            &lt;/li>
            &lt;li>
                &lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;>&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Candara;&quot;>Non-functional requirements - describes conditions and qualities
                for the product or solution to be effective. For example; performance, level of service, reliability, security,
                safety, supportability, etc.&lt;/span>&lt;/font>
            &lt;/li>
            &lt;li>
                &lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;>&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Candara;&quot;>Transition requirements - those temporary capabilities, such as
                training or data conversion requirements, needed to transition from the current state to future
                state.&lt;/span>&lt;/font>
            &lt;/li>
            &lt;li>
                &lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;>&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Candara;&quot;>Project requirements - the project norms or other conditions the
                project needs to function&lt;/span>&lt;/font>
            &lt;/li>
            &lt;li>
                &lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;>&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Candara;&quot;>Quality requirements - conditions or criteria needed to validate
                the successful completion of the project deliverables.&lt;/span>&lt;/font>&lt;br />
            &lt;/li>
        &lt;/ul></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription>
